SCALES
Five forms of the major scale
Same scale, different hand positions. Guitar has many routes to the same note.
PHILOSOPHY
Three components of music
Theory, technique, musicality. Three different skills, three different practices.
SCALES
The major scale formula
A fixed pattern of steps — W-W-H-W-W-W-H — that gives the scale its happy character.
SCALES
The natural minor scale
Same notes as its relative major, different starting point. Sounds sad.
CHORDS
Triads — 1-3-5 chord formula
Every basic chord is built from three notes: root, 3rd, 5th of a scale.
HARMONY
The third determines everything
One note decides whether a chord sounds major or minor. The most important note in a chord.
HARMONY
Diatonic harmony
All chords inside a key. The pattern I-ii-iii-IV-V-vi-vii° works in every major key.
HARMONY
Tension and release
Music's emotional engine. V wants to resolve to I.
PHILOSOPHY
Thinking in numbers, not notes
Scale degrees over note names. Functional thinking instead of absolute thinking.
